SECTION 10.(a) G.S. 130A-343(g) reads as rewritten:
"(g) Innovative Systems. – A manufacturer of a wastewater system for on-site subsurface
use may apply for and be considered for innovative system status by the Department in one of
the following ways:
(1) If the wastewater system has been approved as a provisional wastewater
system pursuant to subsection (f) of this section, the manufacturer may apply
to have the system approved as an innovative wastewater system based on
successful completion of the evaluation protocols established pursuant to
subsection (d) of this section.
(2) If the wastewater system has not been evaluated or approved as a provisional
wastewater system pursuant to subsection (f) of this section, the manufacturer
may apply to the Department to have the system approved as an innovative
wastewater system on the basis of comparable research and testing conducted
in other states. The manufacturer shall provide the Department with the data
and findings of all evaluations of the performance of the system that have been
conducted in any state by or on behalf of the manufacturer. The manufacturer
shall also provide the Department with a summary of the data and findings of
all other evaluations of the performance of the system that are known to the
manufacturer.
